            <h3>The Weekend Format</h3>
            <p>A Grand Prix weekend takes place over three days. <strong>Friday</strong> is for Practice. <strong>Saturday</strong> is Qualifying, where drivers battle for grid position. <strong>Sunday</strong> is the main Race, covering roughly 300km (190 miles).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <h3>The Points System</h3>
            <p>Only the top 10 drivers score points. The winner gets 25 points, second place gets 18, and tenth place gets 1. The driver with the most points at the end of the year becomes the World Champion.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <h3>The Pit Stops</h3>
            <p>F1 pit crews are the fastest in the world. They can change all four tyres in under <strong>2.0 seconds</strong>. A bad pit stop can cost a driver the entire race.</p>
